          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does UGC help SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. UGC provides fresh, unique content that search engines index — particularly reviews, forum threads, and Q&amp;A pages. It also generates long-tail keyword coverage naturally, since users describe products and problems in their own words. Review schema markup on UGC can produce star ratings in search results, improving CTR.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between UGC and influencer content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Traditional UGC is organic and unpaid — a customer posting about a product they love. Influencer content is commissioned and paid. Some brands now use the term 'UGC creator' to describe freelancers who produce content in an authentic, non-polished style — technically paid but designed to look organic.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do you get more user-generated content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
